Definition: of spoken and written language) adhering to traditional standards of correctness and without casual, contracted, and colloquial forms
Example: the paper was written in formal English
Synonyms: INFORMAL, RHETORICAL, noun, attribute, formality, of, spoken, and, written, language, adhering, to, traditional, standards, correctness, without, casual, contracted, colloquial, forms, the, paper, was, in, formal, English
Category: adj.all
